[Black "Ruy Lopez with 4.Bxc6 and 5.Nxe5"]
[Result "*"]

{ 1.e4  is by far the most popular move at the 1600-level. We don't want to give White the opportunity to also play d4 next move and get a strong center and the flexibility to develop the bishops and queen. We will counter with  1...e5  .   As a rule of thumb, we play 1...e5 against any first move from White except in cases where White plays  1.d4  or  1.Nf3  since in those cases it blunders a pawn. Instead, we put our other pawn in the center with  1...d5  . }
1. e4
{ White puts the pawn in the center and opens the diagonals for the bishop and queen. }
1... e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Bb5
{ The Ruy Lopez, also known as The Spanish. } 3... a6
{ The Morphy Defence is the most popular response to the Ruy Lopez. We are forcing White to decide what to do with the light-squared bishop. }
4. Bxc6
{ The Exchange Variation. We are happy to trade our knight for the bishop! }
4... dxc6
{ By capturing with the d-pawn, we open lines for our light-squared bishop and queen. }
5. Nxe5 { The most popular move at the 1600-level and a significant mistake. }
5... Qe7
{ A sneaky move attacking the knight. In the database, by far the most popular move is  5...Qd4  when after  6.Nf3  Qxe4+  Black regains the pawn and has a better position.   After  5...Qe7  White's best reply is  6.Nf3  when after  6...Qxe4+  we reach that same position.   With  5...Qe7  we want to provoke White into making another mistake. }
6. d4
{ In 74% of the games at the 1600-level, White played  6.d4  , however, this is a mistake.  6.Nf3  Qxe4+  7.Qe2  Qxe2+  8.Kxe2  Bg4  would be the best way to play for White, though Black keeps an advantage. This is covered here. }
6... f6
{ We attack the knight again!  7.Qh5  is the most popular move at the 1600-level, which seems very strong. However, it's a blunder because Black wins a piece after  7...g6  8.Nxg6  Qxe4+  9.Be3  Qxg6!  Find the details for that variation here.   After  7.Nf3  Qxe4+  Black also has a significant advantage. This variation is covered here. }
