1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Bc4 Nf6
{ We develop and attack the e4-pawn. This is called the Two Knights Defense. }
4. O-O { White doesn't defend the e4-pawn. } 4... Nxe4
{ It's safe to capture the pawn. } 5. Re1 d5
{ Attacking the bishop, defending the knight, and gaining more control in the center. }
6. Bb5 { White pins the knight. } 6... Bc5
{ Black makes use of the centralized knight and keeps attacking. We are threatening ...Bxf2 and are ready to castle. White's best move is  7.d4  when after  7...exd4  8.Nxd4?  is the most-played move at the 1600-level and a big mistake since after  8...O-O  9.Bxc6  Nxf2  is a deadly blow  10.Kxf2  Qh4+  forks the king and the knight and Black is winning. }
