6... Na5
{ Attacking White's strong light-squared bishop. Here, the same rule applies: we don't have to take the bishop quickly unless White tries to escape by playing a3 or a4. We are ready to play ...c6 and ...d5 next, gaining control in the center! If the bishop tries to escape with  7.Bb5  c6  8.Ba4  b5  , White has to play  9.Bb3  and go back to a square where the knight can capture the bishop. }
