{ A brilliant move, chasing the bishop away to regain control in the center. We shouldn't play  5...Nxd5  because then White has among others the powerful  6.Nxf7  Kxf7  7.Qf3+  , attacking the king and increasing pressure on the knight on d5. }
6. Bb3 Nd4
{ The knight is great in the center, and Black can continue attacking with ...Bg4 and ...Bc5. }
7. O-O Bc5
{ Developing the bishop and preparing to castle! Also, ...Bg4 will be a good developing move, attacking the queen. We shouldn't immediately capture White's light-squared bishop with  7...Nxb3  as the bishop is currently blocked by its d5-pawn, whereas our knight is powerful in the center and can come in handy to harass White's misplaced knight on g5. }
