[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Bc4 Nf6
{ We develop and attack the e4-pawn. This is called the Two Knights Defense. }
4. Ng5
{ This attacking move is the most popular move at the 1600-level! We will make sure that this risky approach from White backfires. }
4... d5
{ It's essential to block the bishop's diagonal to f7 and counter-attack in the center. }
5. exd5 b5
{ A brilliant move, chasing the bishop away to regain control in the center. We shouldn't play  5...Nxd5  because then White has among others the powerful  6.Nxf7  Kxf7  7.Qf3+  , attacking the king and increasing pressure on the knight on d5. }
6. Bf1
{ A challenging move to find, which is the only way to keep an advantage for White. }
6... Nd4
{ Bringing the knight to an attacking position and defending the b5-pawn. } 7.
c3 { White attacks the knight. It's time for a counter-attack. } 7... Nxd5
{ Grabbing the pawn in the center and attacking the knight on g5. } 8. cxd4
Qxg5 9. Bxb5+ { White grabs the pawn with check. } 9... Kd8
{ We sidestep the check. We shouldn't trade bishops with  9...Bd7  10.Bxd7+  Kxd7  because we need our light-squared bishop to attack. }
10. Qf3 { White attacks the knight on d5! } 10... exd4
{ A cunning reply, we capture the pawn and defend the knight with the queen. }
11. Bc6
{ Double attack on the rook and knight, but we don't need to worry about the material here. }
11... Nf4
{ A brilliant move, leaving the rook undefended and going for the attack. } 12.
Bxa8
{ It's so attractive to capture the rook for White. And Black is winning again! }
12... Bg4
{ Developing the bishop with tempo! We plan to develop with ...Bd6 and ...Re8 harassing the king. Black has a deadly attack and a winning position.  The best move for White is  13.h4  when after  13...Bxf3  14.hxg5  Bxa8  Black is doing very well in the endgame.   After  13.Qe4  Bd6  we will play ...Re8 next with a devasting attack. }
