{ By far the most played move at the 1600-level! White should have retreated with Bf1. }
6... Qxd5
{ Recapturing the pawn and attacking the bishop as well as the g2-pawn. } 7.
Bxc6+ Qxc6 { We are still threatening to capture on g2. } 8. Qf3 e4
{ Attacking the queen. } 9. Qb3 h6
{ A spectacular move. We are not afraid that White will capture the f7-pawn. }
10. Nxf7 Be6 { Double attack on the queen and knight! } 11. Ne5
{ A strong counter-attack from White. All other moves are losing. } 11... Qa6
{ This is a lovely square for the queen. We prevent White from castling. We plan to play ...Bd6, developing and attacking the knight. }
