{ Unfortunately, our centralized knight is pinned. How should we solve that? }
11... Rb8
{ Threatening to create a deadly discovered attack with ...Nf4 or ...Ne3, which attacks the queens and aims all forces towards the g2-pawn and the White's king. }
12. dxe5 Ne3
{ A stunning move! Attacking the queen and after  13.Qxe3  Qxg2  is mate. White has to be precise. }
13. Qh3
{ White's only good move, and suddenly White is threatening mate with Qd7 mate! We have to be careful now and trade the queens. }
13... Qxg2+ 14. Qxg2 Nxg2
{ White played everything perfectly, and still, White has only one move in this position to maintain the advantage. }
15. d4
{ From move 5, White needs to find all these only moves to keep an advantage! These are ten only moves. Nobody at the 1600-level ever managed to reach this position. }
15... f6
{ Countering in the center and preventing the attack with Bg5. We plan to play ...Nh4 followed by a deadly check with ...Nf3+. }
