{ What typical motif do we have here? } 7... h6
{ Hunting the misplaced knight! } 8. Nf3 e4 { Continuing our knight hunt! } 9.
Ne5 Bd6
{ We keep on hunting White's knight and kindly invite them to capture the c4-pawn. }
10. Nxc4
{ And now it's time to show White they cannot just move their knight all the time. }
10... Bxh2+ { A brilliant bishop sacrifice also known as the Greek gift. } 11.
Kxh2 Ng4+
{ When the king goes back with  12.Kg1  we play  12...Qh4  threatening checkmate with ...Qh2#.   Also  12.Kh3  is not a good idea for White when  12...Nxf2+  wins the queen with a discovered check.   That's why White's best defensive try is  12.Kg3  , we destroy him with  12...h5  followed by ...h4+. This chases the king to the h3-square when we have the same discovered check motif to win the queen. }
12. Kg1 Qh4 { Deadly mating threat! } *

