{ What typical motif do we have here? } 7... h6
{ Hunting the misplaced knight! } 8. Nf3 e4 { Continuing our knight hunt! } 9.
Re1 { White pins the e-pawn to safeguard the knight temporarily. } 9... Be6
{ Unpinning the e4-pawn and reinforcing the threat on the knight. This is stronger than  9...Be7  since we would like to play our dark-squared bishop to  d6  , setting up threats against White's king. }
10. Ne5 Bd6
{ We develop with tempo and hunt White's knight again. Black has a massive lead in development and a winning position. }
