{ We bring the knight into the attack and plan to go to f4. There is no need to worry about our light-squared bishop since White will get mated on the h-file, or at least lose a lot of material after capturing the bishop. }
9. Qe1 Ng6
{ Bringing the knight into the attack and opening the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop. }
10. Nh2 Nf4
{ Black brought another piece to the attack, and White still can't take the bishop. Black threatens ...Bxh3 when after gxh3, there is a deadly check with ...Qg6. You can find a similar position in the Model Games chapter, here. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2a) Ruy Lopez"]
[Black "Ruy Lopez with 4.Bxc6 and 5.O-O #4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Bb5
{ The Ruy Lopez, also known as The Spanish. } 3... a6
{ The Morphy Defence is the most popular response to the Ruy Lopez. We are forcing White to decide what to do with the light-squared bishop. }
4. Bxc6
{ The Exchange Variation. We are happy to trade our knight for the bishop! }
4... dxc6
{ By capturing with the d-pawn, we open lines for our light-squared bishop and queen. }
5. O-O { By castling, White threatens to play Nxe5 on the next move. } 5... Bg4
{ Pinning the knight and preventing Nxe5. } 6. h3
{ White attacks the bishop and tries to get rid of the pin. } 6... h5
{ A brilliant move, White wanted us to move the bishop, and we are not willing to go along with their plan! We kindly invite White to capture the bishop. If White has already castled, ...h5 is our typical reply to h3 in the Exchange Variation. }
7. d3 Qf6
{ Increasing the pressure on the f3-knight and preparing to castle queenside. }
8. Nbd2
{ White supports the knight. After  8.Bg5  , we again win a piece with the same tactic:  8...Bxf3  eliminates the defender of the bishop and attacks the queen. }
8... Ne7
{ We bring the knight into the attack and plan to go to f4. There is no need to worry about our light-squared bishop since White will get mated on the h-file, or at least lose a lot of material after capturing the bishop. }
9. hxg4 hxg4
{ Black threatens ...Qh6 followed by ...Qh1# mate, as well as to capture the knight. }
10. Nh2 Qh4
{ Black has a devastating attack along the h-file and a winning position. } *

