[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Bb5
{ The Ruy Lopez, also known as The Spanish. } 3... a6
{ The Morphy Defence is the most popular response to the Ruy Lopez. We are forcing White to decide what to do with the light-squared bishop. }
4. Bxc6
{ The Exchange Variation. We are happy to trade our knight for the bishop! }
4... dxc6
{ By capturing with the d-pawn, we open lines for our light-squared bishop and queen. }
5. d3 { By protecting the e4-pawn, White threatens to capture the e5-pawn. }
5... Qf6
{ We defend the e5-pawn and also prepare to attack on the kingside. Pinning the knight now with  5...Bg4  would run into  6.h3  and after  6...Bh5  7.g4  Bg6  8.Nxe5  , White wins a pawn. We want to delay ...Bg4 till White has castled so that we can answer h3 with ...h5. }
6. Bg5
{ White attacks the queen and develops with tempo. This is the most popular move at the 1600-level. It's a risky move by White because we have a cunning reply. }
6... Qg6 { Pinning White's bishop, threatening ...h6. } 7. O-O Bh3
{ A spectacular move. White's bishop cannot move because of ...Qxg2# mate. } 8.
gxh3 h6
{ Pinning and winning back the bishop. Our rook will be activated as well by ...hxg5. Black has an advantage because of White's broken pawn structure in front of the king. }
