{ The most popular move at 1600-level, but this is a bit slow. After  11.Be3  , we again play  11...f6  , kicking White's knight away from the central e5-square. After  12.Nf3  or other knight retreats, we play  12...Re8  , bringing the rook to the center, and Black has a slight advantage. }
11... c5 { We attack the center by putting pressure on d4. } 12. Ndf3 cxd4
{ We trade our doubled c-pawn for White's central pawn. } 13. Nxd4 Nxd4
{ By trading the knight, we give White an isolated d4-pawn. } 14. cxd4
{ After  14.Qxd4  , we trade the queens with  14...Qxd4  , giving White an isolated d-pawn. After  15.cxd4  , we play  15...Be6  with the plan to place the bishop on the great d5-square. }
14... Be6
{ We bring the bishop to the great d5-square. Here it is placed in the center of the board, attacking the g2-pawn, and none of White's pawns can attack it. }
