[FEN "r1b1kbnr/1pp2ppp/p1p3q1/4p1B1/4P3/3P1N2/PPP2PPP/RN1Q1RK1 b kq - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Our queen found a nice spot to attack from. How can we develop a piece in an attacking way? }
7... Bh3
{ A spectacular move. White's dark-squared bishop cannot move because of ...Qxg2# mate. }
8. gxh3 { What's the best way to win the bishop? } 8... h6
{ Pinning and winning back the bishop. After ...hxg5 also, our rook is activated. Black has an advantage because of White's broken pawn structure in front of the king. }
*

