[Black "Exercise 5: Ruy Lopez"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2qkbnr/1pp2pp1/p1p5/4p2p/4P1P1/5N2/PPPP1PP1/RNBQ1RK1 b kq - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Black just sacrificed a piece and wants to start attacking the White king. }
7... hxg4 8. Nxe5
{ The most popular move at the 1600-level, and we already have a forced checkmate. White's best try is to give the piece back with for example  8.d3  gxf3  when after  9.Qxf3  Qh4  10.Qh3  Qxh3  11.gxh3  Rxh3  Black is a pawn-up. }
8... Qh4 { Threatening ...Qh1# mate. } 9. f3
{ White tries to create an escape square for the king, we will stop their plan. How can we prevent the White king from fleeing? }
9... g3
{ Taking away White's escape square and ...Qh1# is mate on the next move. White can block  9...Bc5  with  10.d4  .   9...Qh1+  doesn't work either since White can escape with  10.Kf2  . }
10. Re1 Qh1# { Mate! } *

