1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. d4
{ White immediately puts pressure on the e5-pawn. We should capture the d4-pawn to get rid of the pressure. }
3... exd4 4. Bc4
{ The Scotch gambit. This is my recommendation in the White course, and we have to take it seriously. }
4... Nf6 { Developing and attacking the e4-pawn. } 5. Nxd4 Nxe4
{ It's safe to capture the e4-pawn. } 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. O-O d5
{ A useful move, attacking White's bishop, defending the knight on e4, and also preparing to develop our light-squared bishop. }
*

