{ We grab the e4-pawn. We can defend against the pin along the e-file. } 6. Re1
d5 { Attacking the bishop and defending the knight! } 7. Bxd5
{ White sacrifices the bishop, but will soon regain the piece. } 7... Qxd5 8.
Nc3
{ A spectacular move from White. We cannot capture the knight since White pins our knight and pawn. }
8... Qh5 9. Nxe4
{ 9.Rxe4+  is not dangerous we block with  9...Be6  and prepare to castle queenside and place our rook on the d-file. }
9... Be6
{ Preparing to castle queenside. After  10.Neg5  O-O-O  11.Nxe6  fxe6  12.Rxe6  Bd6  , Black has a nice position.   After  10.Bg5  , we play  10...Bb4!  , attacking the rook on e1 and preparing to castle kingside. }
