1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move from White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. d4
{ White immediately puts pressure on the e5-pawn. We should capture the d4-pawn to get rid of the pressure. }
3... exd4 4. Nxd4 Bc5
{ Attacking the knight!  4...Nxd4  would be a mistake since, after  5.Qxd4  , White's queen is great in the center attacking the g7-pawn, which prevents our dark-squared bishop from developing. }
5. Be3
{ White has a strong threat to capture our knight with Nxc6, which is a discovered attack on the bishop on c5. }
5... Qf6
{ Anticipating White's plan.  5...Nxd4  6.Bxd4  Bxd4  7.Qxd4  wouldn't be good for Black since White's queen is powerful in the center and attacking the g7-pawn. }
6. c3 Nge7
{ Developing the knight and preparing to castle. Also, we prepare to strike in the center with ...d5. }
7. Be2 d5
{ A strong move. Black strikes in the center and opens up the diagonal for the light-squared bishop. }
8. exd5 Nxd5
{ Threatening to capture White's light-squared bishop and break the pawn structure. }
9. O-O Nxe3 10. fxe3 Qh6
{ Attacking the e3-pawn. We will castle soon to safeguard our king. Black has a significant advantage. }
