{ After  8.Ba4  , we can play  8...b5  , attacking the bishop again and freeing the b7-square to develop our light-squared bishop. }
8... Nxc6
{ We reinforce the pressure on the center. The game could continue with  9.O-O  O-O  10.Nxc6  Bxe3!  , weakening White's pawn structure. After  11.fxe3  , White attacks our queen, so we have to use the queen to recapture the knight  11...Qxc6  .  Black has a significant advantage since White's pawn structure is weak. }
