[Black "Ponziani Opening"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. c3
{ The Ponziani Opening. White wants to play d4 next and create a strong center. }
3... d5
{ It's typical in our repertoire to play both ...e5 and ...d5 quickly. By doing so, we can easily develop our bishops and queen. }
4. exd5
{ After  4.Qa4  we can play  4...Bd7  setting up a discovered attack against the queen. After  5.exd5  Nd4  6.Qd1  Nxf3+  7.Qxf3  Nf6  Black has a significant lead in development in return for the pawn.   4.Bb5  is not good for White when after  4...dxe4  5.Nxe5  Qg5!  We pin the knight to the bishop and attack the g2-pawn. }
4... Qxd5 { We threaten ...e4. White already has trouble parrying this. } *

