1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Nc3
{ White develops the other knight. } 3... Nf6
{ We are going for the four knights game. } 4. Bc4
{ The fourth knights Italian. This is the most popular move at the 1600-level, which is not so strong. We transpose to the Italian opening. }
4... Nxe4
{ We can capture the e4-pawn since after  5.Nxe4  we play  5...d5  forking the knight and the bishop. This variation has already been covered here in the chapter regarding the Italian opening. }
