[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Four Knights Scotch #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Nc3
{ White develops the other knight. } 3... Nf6
{ We are going for the four knights game. } 4. d4 { The four knights Scotch! }
4... exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4
{ We create a strong pin on the knight and are threatening to win the e4-pawn. We don't play  5...Bc5  like in the Scotch since pinning the knight is stronger. }
6. Nxc6 bxc6
{ This time, we recapture with the b-pawn since  6...dxc6  allows  7.Qxd8+  and after  7...Kxd8  we lose our right to castle. }
7. Bd3 O-O { Safeguarding the king! } 8. O-O d5
{ Putting the other pawn in the center. } 9. e5 Ng4
{ Black threatens to win the e5-pawn and has a great position. We punish the frequent mistake  10.f4  with  10...Bc5  11.Kh1  Qh4  threatening mate and after  12.h3  Qg3  reinforcing the mate threat White has to give up the queen with  13.Qxg4  Bxg4  Black wins the queen! }
*

