[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Four Knights Ruy Lopez #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Nf3
{ White develops and attacks the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6
{ Developing and defending the e5-pawn. } 3. Nc3
{ White develops the other knight. } 3... Nf6
{ We are going for the four knights game. } 4. Bb5
{ The four knights Ruy Lopez! } 4... Nd4
{ We immediately put pressure on White's strong light-squared bishop. We shouldn't go for  4...a6  since White already protected the e4-pawn and can play  5.Bxc6  bxc6  6.Nxe5  to win a pawn. }
5. Nxe5
{ The second most popular move at the 1600-level and a mistake. We attack along the e-file. After  5.Bc4  we can develop with  5...Bc5  sacrificing the pawn when after  6.Nxe5  Qe7  7.Nf3  d5  breaks open the center to develop our bishop and after  8.Bxd5  Bg4  we are pinning the knight. In the model game GM Yu had a fantastic win against GM Adbihban.   After  5.Ba4  Bc5  6.Nxe5  O-O  Now that White played Ba4 it's stronger to castle immediately because we want to unpin the d-pawn and now after  7.O-O  d6  8.Nf3  Bg4  Black has a deadly pin on the knight. }
5... Qe7 6. f4 Nxb5 { We trade White's strong light-squared bishop. } 7. Nxb5
{ White threatens Nxc7+ with a fork! } 7... d6
{ We attack the knight and defend the c7-pawn with the queen. } 8. Nf3 Qxe4+
{ We capture the pawn with a check! } 9. Qe2 Qxe2+
{ We trade the queens and make sure White cannot castle anymore. } 10. Kxe2 Nd5
{ We defend the c7-pawn. After  11.c4  , the most popular move at the 1600-level, we can play  11...Nxf4+  winning a pawn with check and after  12.Ke3  , we play  12...Ne6  defending the c7-pawn again. Black has a huge advantage. }
*

