[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "King's Gambit #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. f4
{ The King's Gambit. White plays risky chess by opening up diagonals towards the king. }
2... exf4
{ Opening up the kingside and immediately threatening a deadly check with ...Qh4+! }
3. Nf3
{ Preventing ...Qh4+. After White plays  3.Bc4  allowing  3...Qh4+  4.Kf1  we develop and attack with  4...Nf6  when after  5.Nf3  Qh6  we support the f4-pawn and plan to continue development with ...d6, ...Be7 and ...O-O. }
3... d5
{ As usual, we quickly play ...d5! By playing both ...e5 and ...d5 early, we ensure that we can develop all our pieces. }
4. e5
{ The second most popular move at the 1600-level and a significant mistake. }
4... g5 { We support the f4-pawn and threaten ...g4, kicking away the knight! }
5. d4 g4
{ Black is already winning. The best and most played move is  6.Bxf4  , after which we win the knight with  6...gxf3  .  After  7.Qxf3  , we can move out of White's attack by castling queenside with, for example,  7...Be6  8.Bd3  Nc6  9.c3  Qd7  10.O-O  O-O-O  . }
*

