[Black "Center Game: 2.d4 with 3.Qxd4 "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. d4
{ White plays an early d4! We will capture the pawn. } 2... exd4 3. Qxd4
{ White's queen is not well placed. After  3.Nf3  Nc6  we transpose to the Scotch opening. }
3... Nc6
{ Black gains a tempo on the queen! After the queen moves to safety, we will play ...Nf6 and quickly develop the dark-squared bishop and castle. White's best move is  4.Qe3  when after  4...Nf6  5.Nc3  Bb4  is strong pinning the knight and preparing to castle. When we are castled we can play ...d5 to open the center and attack the exposed queen and king on the e-file. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Danish Gambit: 2.d4 with 3.c3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. d4
{ White plays an early d4! We will capture the pawn. } 2... exd4 3. c3
{ The Danish Gambit. White wants to play attacking chess and sacrifice a pawn. }
3... d5
{ The Capablanca Defense. We open the diagonals to be able to develop all pieces. }
4. Qxd4 { White attacks the d5-pawn. } 4... Nf6
{ Developing and defending the d5-pawn. } 5. Bg5 { White pins the knight. }
5... Nbd7
{ A lovely move, supporting the pinned knight and also threatening ...Bc5 developing with tempo. }
6. e5
{ White attacks the pinned f6-knight. However, tactics won't work out for White.  6.exd5  is not dangerous we develop with tempo with  6...Bc5  and after  7.Bxf6  Qxf6  8.Qxf6  Nxf6  Black will regain the pawn and has a better position. }
6... Bc5 { Developing with tempo. } 7. Qf4
{ White's only move to keep on defending the e5-pawn. } 7... Qe7
{ Pinning the e5-pawn, so that White can no longer win the knight. Black has a massive lead in development and a huge advantage. After  8.Nf3  , we can play  8...h6  , forcing  9.Bxf6  gxf6  . This attacks the e5-pawn another time, thus winning it. }
*

