[Black "Danish Gambit: 2.d4 with 3.c3 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. d4
{ White plays an early d4! We will capture the pawn. } 2... exd4 3. c3
{ The Danish Gambit. White wants to play attacking chess and sacrifice a pawn. }
3... d5
{ The Capablanca Defense. We open the diagonals to be able to develop all pieces. }
4. Qxd4 { White attacks the d5-pawn. } 4... Nf6
{ Developing and defending the d5-pawn. } 5. e5 Ne4
{ Black has parried White's initiative and is already starting an attack himself. We threaten ...Bc5 attacking the queen and the f2-pawn. }
6. Nf3
{ The most played move at the 1600-level, losing the important f2-pawn. All other popular moves at the 1600-level are big mistakes as well; they all allow ...Bc5. }
6... Bc5
{ Attacking the queen and increasing the pressure on the f2-pawn. Black has a winning position. }
