[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Danish Gambit: 2.d4 with 3.c3 #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. d4
{ White plays an early d4! We will capture the pawn. } 2... exd4 3. c3
{ The Danish Gambit. White wants to play attacking chess and sacrifice a pawn. }
3... d5
{ The Capablanca Defense. We open the diagonals to be able to develop all pieces. }
4. exd5
{ White should recapture the pawn. We are a pawn up after  4.e5  dxc3   Also, after  4.cxd4  dxe4  , Black is a pawn up without any compensation for White. }
4... Qxd5 5. cxd4 Nc6
{ Black starts attacking the isolated d4-pawn. We transpose to the Albin Countergambit, our recommendation against 1.d4. This variation is covered in more detail here in the chapter regarding the Albin Countergambit. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Bishop's Opening: 2.Bc4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Bc4
{ This will likely transpose to the Italian. } 2... Nf6
{ We develop the knight and attack the e4-pawn. } 3. Nf3
{ When White plays  3.d4  going for the Urusov gambit we reply with  3...exd4  when after  4.Nf3  Nc6  we transpose to the Scotch Gambit.   After  3.Nc3  we can go for the same trick as we saw in the Italian opening with  3...Nxe4  when after  4.Nxe4  d5  Black regains the piece and has a great position. }
3... Nxe4 4. Nxe5
{ White captures the pawn and threatens Nxf7. After  4.Nc3  , White plays the reversed Stafford Gambit. I would recommend  4...Nc6  with a transposition to the four knights Italian. After  5.Nxe4  we regain the piece with the double attack  5...d5  .  It is very risky to play  4...Nxc3  since White will reply with  5.dxc3  , opening the diagonals for the bishop and queen with good attacking chances. }
4... d5 { We gain a tempo on the bishop and defend against White's threats. }
5. Qf3 { White threatens Qf7# mate. } 5... Be6
{ We develop the bishop and defend against the mate! Black has a better position. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
