[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Bishop's Opening: 2.Bc4 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Bc4
{ This will likely transpose to the Italian. } 2... Nf6
{ We develop the knight and attack the e4-pawn. } 3. d3 Nc6
{ Threatens ...Na5 to trade White's strong light-squared bishop. } 4. Bg5
{ After  4.Nf3  Be7  , we have a transposition to the Italian opening.   When White plays  4.c3  or  4.a3  to create an escape square for the bishop, we reply with  4...d5  and open the diagonal for our light-squared bishop. }
4... Na5 { We trade White's strong light-squared bishop for the knight. } *

