[White "4a) 1.e4 e5 sidelines"]
[Black "Vienna Gambit: 2.Nc3 and 3.f4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 { 1.e4 was a good move by White, let's copy them. } 2. Nc3
{ White develops the knight and defends the e4-pawn. } 2... Nf6
{ We develop the knight and attack the e4-pawn. } 3. f4
{ The Vienna gambit!  3.Bc4  Nc6  will transpose to variations we have seen before. }
3... d5
{ Striking back in the center and opening the diagonal for all our pieces. We shouldn't play  3...exf4  this time, since White has the strong  4.e5  , attacking our knight. }
4. exd5 Nxd5
{ White's king is in danger because White moved the f-pawn forward. After  5.fxe5  Nxc3  6.bxc3  we strike with  6...Qh4+  and White cannot play  7.g3  , since  7...Qe4+  forks and wins the rook. }
