[White "4b) 1.e4 e5 sidelines Tactics and Model games "]
[Black "Exercise 1: 1.e4 e5 Sidelines"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bq1rk1/p1p2ppp/2p5/2bpP3/5Pn1/2NB4/PPP3PP/R1BQ1R1K b - - 0 11"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ The bishop and knight are very active and can work together to win the exchange, but don't we have a stronger attack? }
11... Qh4
{ 11...Nf2+  is also quite good, winning the exchange. But mate is better! }
12. h3 Qg3
{ Reinforcing the threat of ...Qh2# mate.  12...Nf2+  only wins the exchange. }
13. hxg4
{ White best move would be  13.Qxg4  when after  13...Bxg4  White gave up the queen to prevent mate. Black has a winning position. }
13... Qh4# { Finishing the attack with a fantastic mate! } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4b) 1.e4 e5 sidelines Tactics and Model games "]
[Black "Exercise 2: 1.e4 e5 Sidelines"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqkb1r/pppp1ppp/5n2/1B2N3/3nP3/2N5/PPPP1PPP/R1BQK2R b KQkq - 0 5"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White just took the e5-pawn. How can we bring in another piece to punish it? }
5... Qe7 { Attacking the knight! } 6. Nf3
{ White's knight on c3 is still defending the e4-pawn. } 6... Nxb5
{ First, we trade White's strong light-squared bishop. } 7. Nxb5
{ White is a pawn up and c7 is hanging. What should we do? } 7... Qxe4+
{ And we capture the pawn with a check! } 8. Qe2 Qxe2+
{ We trade queens and make sure White cannot castle anymore. } 9. Kxe2
{ White is still threatening Nxc7+, so we should defend against this idea. White has a strong threat. What's the best way to defend against it? }
9... Nd5 { Defending the c7-pawn. } 10. c4
{ White chases away our knight! The defender of the c7-pawn is being attacked. How can we survive? }
10... a6 { We counter-attack the knight and have a better position. } *

