[White "5b) Albin Countergambit Tactics and Model games "]
[Black "Exercise 1: Albin Countergambit"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1k1nr/ppp2ppp/2n5/3qp3/3P4/2B2N2/PP2PPPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ #  (How can we slow down White's development?) } 7... e4
{ We are hunting the knight and also make sure that White's dark-squared bishop is stuck behind the d4-pawn. }
8. Ne5 e3
{ A brilliant prophylactic move with the idea to prevent White's light-squared bishop, which also prevents White from castling kingside. }
9. fxe3
{ At the 1600-level in all games, White captured the pawn even though this is a mistake. }
9... Nf6
{ Black has a lovely position since White's light-squared bishop is out of play. We plan to place the knight on the e4-square, where none of the White's pawns can attack it. Also, we are ready to castle kingside. }
