[White "6c) London and Reti: Tactics and Model games  "]
[Black "Exercise 2: 1.Nf3 1.c4 and sidelines"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2qkbnr/ppp2ppp/2n5/3p1b2/3P4/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 0 6"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ What is the typical idea here? } 6... Nb4
{ We go for the fork threatening ...Nc2+ attacking the king and rook, and White is in trouble. }
7. e4 { White blocks the bishop's diagonal, preventing the fork. } 7... Bxe4
{ By capturing with the bishop, we reinforce the threat of ...Nc2+. } 8. Nxe4
dxe4 { We attack the knight. } 9. Ng5 Qxd4
{ A classy tactical combination. Our queen is indirectly protected because we have the fork. }
10. Qxd4 Nc2+ { Regaining the queen. } 11. Kd1 Nxd4
{ Black has a dominating position. } 12. Nxe4
{ White tries to regain one of the pawns but is still a pawn down. } 12...
O-O-O
{ Castling queenside immediately places our rook in a powerful position. We threaten ...Nb3+ with a discovered check to win the rook. White is in big trouble. }
