[White "7a) English opening: 1.c4"]
[Black "English Opening: 2.Nc3 with 3.e4"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 e5
{ Let's play the reversed Sicilian. We used the rule of thumb that we play  1...e5  against every more from White except 1.d4 or 1.Nf3 when 1...e5 would blunder the pawn. }
2. Nc3
{ Those of you who also have the White course know that we fight the Sicilian with the Alapin. In this position, it would work yet to go for the reversed Alapin since after  2...c6  , White plays  3.Nf3  attacking our e5-pawn when we don't have our signature knight-hunting move  3...e4  attacking that knight since White captures with  4.Nxe4  .  We keep in mind that we want to go for the Alapin idea later on, but first, we develop the knight. }
2... Nf6 { Developing and also getting ready to castle. } 3. e4
{ By playing e4, White weakens the d4-square. So we are directing our pieces to this strong square. }
3... Bc5 4. Nf3 Ng4
{ It's time to give your opponent a heart attack. We are threatening ...Nxf2+ forking the queen and rook. }
5. d4 { White has to block the bishop's diagonal. } 5... exd4
{ We capture the pawn and attack the knight. } 6. Nxd4
{ The most-played move at 1600-level, however, this is a big mistake. By capturing the d4-pawn, our bishop becomes more powerful, and White allows us a strong sacrifice. The best move for White is  6.Na4  where after  6...Bb4+  7.Bd2  Qe7  Black attacks the e4-pawn and has a slight advantage. }
6... Nxf2
{ We sacrifice on the f2-square, forking the queen and rook. When we sacrifice a piece on the f2-square, we want to have a direct follow-up to regain the material. }
7. Kxf2 Qf6+
{ Double attack on the king and knight. We are forcing the king forward to keep on protecting the knight. }
8. Ke3 Nc6
{ By adding another attacker to the pinned knight, we win back the piece and keep a strong initiative because of White's weak king. Black has a winning position.  After  9.Ncb5  O-O  White's knight keeps on being pinned, and we threaten ...a6 eliminating the defending knight to win the piece. To watch the model game where Grandmaster Ivan Sokolov won an attacking game with Black click here. And also in the German Youth Championships under 10 Farokhi won an impressive game. }
