{ What tactical idea do we have here? } 4... Ng4
{ It's time to give your opponent a heart attack. We are threatening ...Nxf2 forking the queen and rook. }
5. d4 { White has to block the bishop's diagonal. } 5... exd4
{ We capture the pawn and attack the knight. } 6. Nxd4
{ The most-played move at the 1600-level, however, this is a big mistake. By capturing the d4-pawn, our bishop becomes more powerful, and White allows us a strong sacrifice. The best move for White is  6.Na4  when after  6...Bb4+  7.Bd2  Qe7  Black attacks the e4-pawn and has a slight advantage. }
6... Nxf2
{ We sacrifice on the f2-square, forking the queen and rook. When we sacrifice a piece on the f2-square, we want to have a direct follow-up to regain the material. }
7. Kxf2 Qf6+
{ Double attack on the king and knight. We are forcing the king forward to keep on protecting the knight. }
8. Ke3 Nc6
{ By adding another attacker to the pinned knight, we win back the piece and keep a strong initiative because of the White's weak king. Black has a winning position. After  9.Ncb5  O-O  White's knight keeps on being pinned, and we threaten ...a6 eliminating the defending knight to win the piece. }
*

