6. Be2
{ The most popular move at the 1600-level, however, this is s a big blunder. White should play  6.d4  making space for the king when we reply with  6...Qe7  pressuring the e3-pawn. }
6... Bxh2 { We are threatening ...Bg3+, so White has to capture the bishop. }
7. Rxh2 { Capturing with the knight would lead to mate after ...Qh4+. } 7...
Nxh2 { Winning the rook. } 8. Nxh2 Qh4+
{ Our tactical justification, forking the king and the knight. } 9. Kf1 Qxh2
{ We are an exchange up and have a winning position. } *

