{ How can we keep our strong light-squared bishop? } 9... c4
{ A fantastic prophylactic move preventing White from playing Bd3 and exchanging powerful bishop. We outplayed White in the London, and now Black is to only one to remain with a powerful London bishop while we managed to neutralize White's London bishop. When White tries to break down our pawn structure with  10.b3  , we strike with  10...Nb4  threatening ...Nxc2+ when after  11.cxb4  Bxb4+  Black has a devastating attack, and the computer already gives  -8. }
