[SetUp "1"]

{ How can we slow down White's development? } 7... e4
{ We are hunting the knight and also making sure that White's dark-squared bishop is stuck behind the d4-pawn. }
8. Ne5 e3
{ A brilliant prophylactic move with the idea to prevent White's light-squared bishop from developing easily, which also prevents White from castling kingside. }
9. fxe3
{ In all games at the 1600-level, White captured the pawn even though this is a mistake. }
9... Nf6
{ Black has a lovely position since White's light-squared bishop is out of play. We plan to place the knight on the e4-square, where none of the White's pawns can attack it. Also, we are ready to castle kingside. }
