{ White just took the e5-pawn. How can we bring in another piece to punish it? }
5... Qe7 6. Nf3 { White's knight on c3 is still defending the e4-pawn. } 6...
Nxb5 { First, we trade White's strong light-squared bishop. } 7. Nxb5
{ White is a pawn up and threatens Nc7+. } 7... Qxe4+
{ And we capture the pawn with a check! } 8. Qe2 Qxe2+
{ We trade queens and make sure White cannot castle anymore. } 9. Kxe2
{ White is still threatening Nxc7+, so we should defend against this idea. White has a strong threat. What's the best way to defend against it? }
9... Nd5 { Defending the c7-pawn. } 10. c4
{ White chases away our knight! The defender of the c7-pawn is being attacked. How can we survive? }
10... a6 { We counter-attack the knight and have a better position. } *

