[SetUp "1"]

{ What typical motif do we have here? } 7... h6 8. Nf3
{ Continuing our knight hunt! } 8... e4 9. Re1
{ White pins the e-pawn to safeguard the knight temporarily. } 9... Be6
{ Unpinning the e4-pawn and reinforcing the threat on the knight. This is stronger than  9...Be7  since we would like to play our dark-squared ...Bd6 setting up threats against White's king. }
10. Ne5 Bd6
{ We develop with tempo and hunt White's knight again. Black has a massive lead in development and a winning position. }
