[SetUp "1"]

{ White fell for a famous trap. } 4... Nxe4 { We will regain the piece! } 5.
Nxe4
{ White has a lot of pieces in the center. We should do something about that! }
5... d5 { Forking the bishop and knight and gaining control in the center. } 6.
Bb5 { Pinning the knight. } 6... dxe4 7. Nxe5
{ White increases the pressure on the c6-knight, however, we will go for the counter-attack. }
7... Qg5 { Attacking and pinning the knight and also attacking the g2-pawn. }
8. Bxc6+ bxc6 { We are still attacking the knight and the g2-pawn. } 9. Nxc6
Qxg2 { We capture the pawn attack the rook and destroy White's king safety. }
10. Rf1 Bg4
{ Trapping the queen. Play could continue with  11.f3  Bxf3  12.Rxf3  exf3  after which White has to give up the queen to prevent mate. }
