[White "8) Theme based tactics drills "]
[Black "Exercise 45: Albin Countergambit: Minor Promotion"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbqk1nr/ppp2ppp/8/4P3/1BP5/4p3/PP3PPP/RN1QKBNR b KQkq - 0 6"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ How do we win here in a brilliant way? } 6... exf2+
{ A cunning move. White cannot recapture since after  7.Kxf2  Qxd1  wins the queen. }
7. Ke2
{ White places the king on an awkward square to keep protecting the queen. }
7... fxg1=N+
{ This is fantastic. We promote to a knight with a check, giving no time to White to exchange the queens. Promoting to a queen with  7...fxg1Q+  will only result in an equal endgame. When we don't give a check, White plays the intermediate  8.Qxd8+  Kxd8  and then recapture with  9.Rxg1  . }
8. Rxg1
{ White's best move would be  8.Ke1  when we attack with  8...Qh4+  Black is a piece up and also has a devastating attack. }
8... Bg4+
{ This deadly check wins the queen. It wouldn't have won the queen one move ago since White could still block with the knight @@StartFEN@@rnbqk1nr/ppp2ppp/8/4P3/1BP5/8/PP2KpPP/RN1Q1BNR b kq - 1 7@@EndFEN@@  7...Bg4+  8.Nf3  . }
*

